'''Eberhard Schulze''' is a German [[mosaic]] artist.

He was known for his [[underground art]]work with Hans Unger. These mosaic pieces are based on London sites and 
He has also done works of art by himself using resources such as slate and glass. Schulze was forced to give up mosaic-making, when a [[Spinal cord injury|spinal injury]] forced him into [[Retirement|early retirement]]. In 1965, Schulze and Unger created a large mosaic of the crucifixion for St Jude's Catholic church in [[Wigan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stjude-wigan.org.uk/ |title=Saint Jude's Catholic Church, Wigan, Lancashire, England ‘Christ on the Cross’ – Unger/Eber |publisher=Stjude-wigan.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-01-01}}</ref> Between 1962 and 1970, Schulze designed several posters for [[London Transport Board|London Transport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ltmcollection.org/posters/artist/artist.html?IXartist=Eberhard+Schulze |title=Artist: Eberhard Schulze - Poster and poster artwork collection |publisher=London Transport Museum |date= |accessdate=2014-01-01}}</ref>

He went on to develop a successful career as a specialist aquarist, becoming England’s leading [[Discus (fish)|discus fish]] breeder. He has written a book on discus fish called ''Discus Fish - The King of all Aquarium Fish''.

He now lives in [[Nonthaburi (city)|Nonthaburi]] in Thailand.

